"Such cases must be referred to hospital facilities. The treatment of severe malnutrition occurs in three to four stages and their corresponding tasks. 1. Initial treatment: to correct mortality risk factors and metabolic imbalances, and to rectify the digestive function in order to prepare patients for a rich diet that permits quick nutritional rehabilitation. 2. Nutritional rehabilitation: to bring patients up to a satisfactory nutritional level. 3. Resumption of normal feeding: to prepare patients for the diet that will be theirs outside the TFC after their discharge, to ensure that patients maintain a good nutritional and health status during this period. 4."